snippet.textDisplay:
Hats off to Rafaqat Ali & Shiraz Uppal, and of course the Maestro Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan who originally composed this masterpiece. I've heard this naat innumerable times, yet each time I listen to it, it's a new feeling for me. The composition and the lyrics draw you into rapture and ecstasy,  and one feels like dancing like the whirling dervishes with tears flowing effortlessly.
 'Tu Kuja, Man Kuja'. Who are you, and who am I. I am nothing in your presence.  Peace and Love to all.
